**Three-layer fix applied:**

1. **`AppServiceProvider::boot()`** — Added `URL::forceScheme('https')` that activates when behind a reverse proxy (`X-Forwarded-Proto` header present) or when `APP_URL` starts with `https://`

2. **`bootstrap/app.php`** — Added `$middleware->trustProxies(at: '*')` so Laravel trusts the reverse proxy's forwarded headers (proto, host, port) — this is the root cause fix

3. **Layout template** — Added a safety net that intercepts Vite's output and replaces any remaining `http://` URLs with `https://` when the request is detected as secure

